[thinking] **Evaluating native complications**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I think the native compile likely didn't include something because we may not have had the necessary metadata. It seems like external "Forge handles metadata generation" after a successful Java run could create the needed metadata under build, not src. The native failure indicates there's no reflect Object.<init> metadata, and it might be due to needing to register the serializable class at build time. It's strange since the Object constructor shouldn't need it. Maybe adding a system property could help, but it seems serialization in native might not work without the appropriate config.
